reviewText: It was a bit odd watching what was originally titled The Story Lady with Jessica Tandy but not her husband Hume Cronyn. Still, it does have their daughter, Tandy Cronyn, in it as her daughter in the movie. In it, Grace has to move out of her own place and live with her daughter and husband. She wants to be useful and, unable to find a job, finds herself at a local cable recording studio starring in her own show. What unfolds from there I won't say, except you will meet a workaholic mother and her daughter, and learn about the shady practices of unscrupulous businessmen out to make a buck. In the end is the warm feeling you expect at Christmas, and this movie will not let you down. I wish they hadn't renamed it, but it is still the same movie.
summary: The Story Lady With A New Title

reviewText: The original title, The Story Lady, would be more appropriate, but regardless of the title, it is a great family movie.  It includes all the issues many families face ... children of divorce, work pressures, aging but head-strong parents ... and hopefully reminds us what's important in life.  Jessica Tandy delivers a great performance.
